n call it at the end of your controller before it renders the view?\n\nIn any case the after_filter doesn't stop the controller from doing it's thing, it just raises an exception to alert you that you let someone through. You should be finding these holes in tests not in production!\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/comments/70607188/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"exciton","id":1518068,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTgwNjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1518068?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton","html_url":"https://github.com/exciton","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exciton/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/comments/70627751","html_url":"https://github.com/varvet/pundit/issues/207#issuecomment-70627751","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/207","id":70627751,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcwNjI3NzUx","user":{"login":"valscion","id":482561,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ4MjU2MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/482561?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion","html_url":"https://github.com/valscion","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/valscion/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2015-01-20T09:41:21Z","updated_at":"2015-01-20T09:41:21Z","body":"> Couldn't you call verify_policy_scoped before your view renders? As in call it at the end of your controller before it renders the view?\n\nThat would be quite cumbersome, unless you have some nice way of hooking to some callback in Rails to do exactly that. We were just using the `verify_policy_scoped` as a quick aid in finding the controllers which didn't run proper authorizations.\n\n> You should be finding these holes in tests not in production!\n\nThat is true. It just requires too much effort to remember to test each and every one controller action if they haven't been written with TDD in the first place, and even then some code paths might slip past those tests. It should never hurt to have the last line of defense in the shape of automatic error reporting in place.\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/comments/70627751/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"valscion","id":482561,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ4MjU2MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/482561?v=4","gravata